What is Sunflower Oil?
Sunflower oil is a non‑volatile, edible oil extracted from the seeds of the sunflower plant (Helianthus annuus) using either mechanical pressing or solvent extraction techniques. Renowned for its light, neutral taste, high smoke point (typically 225 °C), and a fatty‑acid profile rich in linoleic and oleic acids, it serves as a versatile ingredient in culinary, industrial, and personal‑care formulations. The oil also contains appreciable levels of vitamin E and phytosterols, contributing to its reputation as a heart‑healthy cooking medium.
